gomodel:SYNGO_1810  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"These experiments highlighted a neuronal activity-induced potentiation of GKAP-DLC2 interaction in postsynaptic elements.\" shown with BRET microscopy.. Experimental description: - Cultured neurons are mouse species (\"Hippocampal neuronal primary cultures were prepared from embryonic day 17.5 mice and ....\")\n- Species of overexpressed protein is not mentioned in the paper (\"The DLC2-pCMV-SPORT6 plasmid was purchased from Source BioScience Geneservice Nottingham, UK).\"). Author contacted (julie.perroy@igf.cnrs.fr)) for species information on construct (dd 3/11/2017 Pim). Answer:\n\n\"the DLC2 we used in this paper is the HUMAN DLC2.\nDo not hesitate if I can help you more.\nBest,\nJulie\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1810" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

